4:
After her! She's just a girl—she
couldn't have gotten far!
6:
She's going to learn firsthand what
happens to slaves who bite the
hand that feeds them!
19:
A runaway slave, eh? Looks like she's
still breathing.
30:
More importantly, we need to find
her a place to rest!
46:
I'm Alk. This is Light and Nimbus. And
your name is...?
53:
So I take it this sword's yours? We
picked it up when we found you.
63: Wasn't exactly plannin' on stealing it.
67:
You should rest some more. Let me
ask the owner if they serve any food—
73:
Heh, how 'bout we teach you some
manners?
75:
A talking beast? My, my, you're
going to make quite the souvenir.
84: *huff huff* What was that all about?
88:
I caught sight of this wanted poster
when we ran out of the inn.
90:
"A slave girl attacked her master
and knocked out the guards with
her sword before escaping," it said.
95:
"Knocked out the guards"... Did you
really do that?
99:
I don't know... I was given a sword
during a banquet and told to fight
monsters...
102:
I was so scared... And all of a
sudden...
118: Heh. Try telling that to THEM.
121:
You've caused me quite a bit of
trouble, Nasir.
122:
Every tear you shed, every scream
that escapes your lips—they all
belong to your master. Don't expect
an easy death.
131: Ah... I can hear that voice again...
134: If I'm going to lose everything, then...
137:
I MIGHT AS WELL JUST BURN IT ALL TO
THE GROUND!
153: This is bad! We have to stop her!
164:
BURN, BURN, BUURRRN! DOWN WITH IT
ALL!
179:
Fortunately she's alive. The burns
aren't too bad either.
186:
It's almost like she was possessed.
This sword must've been the culprit.
190:
It's more than that. She did that of
her own free will.
194: Either way, we can't just leave her.
197:
Agreed. The potential risk is far too
great.
199:
Let's bring her back to Starview
Village with us.
203:
You look terrible... Come on now,
there's no need to cry like that...
